  "primerTitle": "Capitals by region",
  "primer": "Each card gives a **country**; recall its **capital city**. The deck spans five regions — here are high-yield anchors per region (the full set is larger).\n\n**Europe** — France → Paris, Germany → Berlin, Spain → Madrid, Italy → Rome, UK → London, Russia → Moscow. *Netherlands → Amsterdam* (capital), though the government sits in The Hague.\n\n**Asia** — China → Beijing, Japan → Tokyo, India → New Delhi, South Korea → Seoul, Indonesia → Jakarta. Watch the **non-largest-city traps**: Turkey → Ankara (not Istanbul); Saudi Arabia → Riyadh; Iran → Tehran.\n\n**Africa** — Egypt → Cairo, Kenya → Nairobi, Ethiopia → Addis Ababa, Morocco → Rabat, Ghana → Accra. Traps: Nigeria → Abuja (not Lagos); South Africa → Pretoria (executive capital).\n\n**Americas** — USA → Washington, D.C., Canada → Ottawa, Mexico → Mexico City, Argentina → Buenos Aires, Peru → Lima, Colombia → Bogotá, Chile → Santiago. Trap: Brazil → Brasília (not Rio).\n\n**Oceania** — Australia → Canberra (not Sydney/Melbourne), New Zealand → Wellington, Fiji → Suva.\n\n**Rule of thumb:** the capital is often *not* the biggest or best-known city — purpose-built or administrative capitals (Brasília, Canberra, Abuja, Ankara) are the classic catches.",
